text: The first half of the trailer completely ruins what actually made that fight special in the movie. It was a (seemingly) single cut, there was no background music, and the only sounds you heard were the ACTUAL sounds of the fights. Grunts, muted thuds, glass breaking, metal clinking, that's it. No exaggerated comic book punching sounds, no tense music, no quick cuts to make the action look faster. Just three people fighting to the point of visible exhaustion. And it's one of the best fight scenes of the past decade because of it, imo.
